1: Download the Arduino IDE
The latest version of the IDE can be downloaded from the official website. Link: www.arduino.cc/en/software

2: Interfacing EMG Sensor

The EMG Sensor is interfaced with Arduino MEGA board.

3: Verify the device
Open device manager in your PC and expand the ports, you should see that the Arduino MEGA board is detected, if not you need to install the required drivers.

4: Compile your sketch
Open the file which contains the source code. Hit the compile button in the top- left corner of the IDE. You should see that the code is compiled successfully without any errors.

5: Upload the sketch
Hit the upload button. Now while the code uploads, you should see the LED in the board blinking indicating data transfer between the board and the computer.

6: Output
The Prosthetic Arm opens and closes the finger according to the EMG data and the servo motor rotates according to it
